body_html:
Andrehentz, thanks for the feedback!
I happened find this answer by Peter Warden on stack overflow:
float-ops-found-in-quantized-tensorflow-mobilenet-model

He said because quantized_depthwise_conv was not supported by Tensorflow, so the "graph_transform" wouldn't generate the corresponding quantized operation for the mobilenet.
Not quite sure if the TOCO also obeys this rule so that when it transforms the quant_mobilenet tflite into protobuf, it changes the quantized depthwise_conv op into floating point one.

body:
Andrehentz, thanks for the feedback!  
I happened find this answer by Peter Warden on stack overflow: 
[float-ops-found-in-quantized-tensorflow-mobilenet-model](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/48121702/float-ops-found-in-quantized-tensorflow-mobilenet-model)


He said because quantized_depthwise_conv was not supported by Tensorflow,  so the "graph_transform" wouldn't generate the corresponding quantized operation for the mobilenet.
Not quite sure if the TOCO also obeys this rule so that when it transforms the quant_mobilenet tflite into protobuf, it changes the quantized depthwise_conv op into floating point one.
